definition.value: A trihydroxybenzoic acid that is benzoic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2, 4 and 6.
A benzoate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-hydroxybenzoic acid with methanol.
An androstanoid that is the acetate derivative of  testosterone.
A bile acid taurine conjugate of  chenodeoxycholic acid.

A one-carbon compound with formula CO2 in which the carbon is attached to each oxygen atom by a double bond. A colourless, odourless gas under normal conditions, it is produced during respiration by all animals, fungi and microorganisms that depend directly or indirectly on living or decaying plants for food.
